{
  "stem": "1169.3",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Number one, they blamed the rabbis, the Hasidic rabbis, who were anti-Zionist, who discouraged people from going on aliyah to settle in Israel.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "If not for them, then we would be in Israel, et cetera, et cetera, et cetera.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] In retrospect, of course, I speak on this subject, and I don't blame anyone for this, because number one, whoever wanted to go, went and went to the rabbi and said, I'm leaving.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Give me a blessing.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "They did not ask.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Those who asked, wanted to hear they should not go.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But that's not even the issue.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "The issue is in today's terms, when we go to Israel today, and we are there in 10 hours, and the moment we get there, we call up.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "When someone went to Israel before the Second World War, chances were he never saw his family ever again.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Chances were he could never speak to them ever again, and it took two months for a letter to arrive.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And we had very close-knit families.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "It was very hard to ask a young boy or girl to leave his family and never to-- never ever to see them again.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "In the context of the-- of those times, I believe our people acted correctly.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "It's difficult to go away from your father and mother, knowing that you will never, ever see them again.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "In fact, when my uncle came to America before the war, his mother told him, my son, I know I will never see you again.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "That was the good-bye.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "But there was a lot of self-recrimination.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And over there, I learned the whole concept of Zionism.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "I had never heard of that before.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
